title: CrockPot Chicken Tacos

ingredients.name: canned diced tomatoes with chiles drained or 1 can Rotel
package taco seasoning or 2 Tablespoons homemade taco seasoning

preparations: Combine salsa, canned tomatoes, and taco seasoning.
Place onions & chicken in the slow cooker and top with tomato mixture.
instructions: Cook on low 7-8 hours or high 3-4 hours.
Remove chicken from slow cooker and shred.
Return to slow cooker and stir in juices.
Serve in taco shells, on salads, pizzas or in bowls over rice!
If you prefer you can skip the canned tomatoes and add 1 ½ cups salsa.
